# Commit Before Test (BLOCKING)

**Do not run any test command** (MCP `RunAllTests`/`RunSomeTests`, `dbs-build --target ...`, `xcodebuild test`, `swift test`, any `run_terminal_cmd` that runs tests) until the working tree is fully committed.

## Sequence

1. `git status` before invoking the test run.
2. If anything is uncommitted: `git add -A` (or add all changed paths) + `git commit -m "<msg>"` so the **entire** working tree is captured — **multi-agent included**.
3. Only then run the test command.

**"I'll commit after the test" is not allowed.** No exceptions.

## What "clean" means (multi-agent)

"Clean" = everything in the working tree is committed (across all agents/sessions). Do **not** use `git stash`, `git restore`, `git checkout --`, `git reset`, `git clean`, or delete files to hide work you didn't make. See [multi-agent-git-boundaries.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/multi-agent-git-boundaries.mdc). **Commit everything** — that's how you get clean.
